    "Telehealth is often used in conjunction with other health care interventions, such as in-person visits or medications, which can make it difficult to separate the impact of telehealth from other factors.",
    "Importantly, there may be biases in the types of patients who are most likely to use telehealth.",
    "Thus, it is difficult to generalize findings to the broader population.",
    "Another subtopic in this topic is organ transplantation.",
    "Research gaps related to this subtopic may be attributed to the following reasons: (1) while there have been some studies on the impact of COVID-19 on organ transplant patients, the number of patients in these studies is often relatively small."
